  • Package j.algo

    • Class j.algo.UnionFind extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -5024744406713321675L

      • Serialized Fields

        • rank

          int[] rank
          rank[i] = Rank of element i. A negative value indicates that the element is a canonical root of the membership set (or tree). The magnitude of the value is the height of the tree (starting from 1). Note that the height is only an upper bound due to path compression. The max possible height is log_2(Integer.MAX_VALUE+1) due to ranking. A non-negative value indicates that the element is a non-root. The value is the zero-based index of its parent in the tree.

        • numDisjoint

          int numDisjoint
          Number of disjoint sets (or trees).
